method.name: refresh
method.comment: Refresh the short live access token. If succeeds, the access token and expiration time value inside this object will be overwritten to new values. requestConfig: request config used to make http request. Return type: @return:DbxRefreshResult which contains app key and app secret.

method.name: startOAuth2PKCE
method.comment: see Auth#startOAuth2PKCE(Context, String, DbxRequestConfig, DbxHost) appInfo:

method.name: aboutToExpire
method.comment: Return type: @return:true if access token is already expired or current time is within the \{@value EXPIRE_MARGIN} to expiration time. returns false if is is null

method.name: Initialize
method.comment: Create a DbxCredential object supporting refreshing short live tokens. accessToken: Short-lived access token from OAuth flow. expiresAt: Expiration time in millisecond from OAuth flow. refreshToken: Refresh token from OAuth flow appKey: You app's client id. appSecret: You app's client secret.

property.name: RefreshToken
property.comment: Return the refresh token which can be used to obtain new access token.

property.name: AccessToken
property.comment: Returns the OAuth access token to use for authorization with Dropbox servers.

property.name: ExpiresAt
property.comment: Return the millisecond when accessToken is going to expire.

method.name: download
method.comment: Downloads the file "path" and store it in the path "localPath" under the filename "localFilename". DEV:Tested

method.name: uploadsession
method.comment:
"path" and "filename" of the Filee with the Size "size" to Upload to Dropbox
if skip is > 0 then skip bytes are skipped when uploading startsessionid defines a SessionId to start with. Usually you should use an empty String here dbxFolder defines the folder on Dropbox to store the File. It will be created if not exist writemode defines the Writemode to use. Possible values are WriteModeADD and WriteModeOVERWRITE

method.name: download2
method.comment: Downloads the file "path" with the revision "rev" and store it in the path "localPath" under the filename "localFilename". DEV:NOT Tested

method.name: listFolderContinue
method.comment: Once a cursor has been retrieved from {@link DbxUserFilesRequests#listFolder(String)}, use this to paginate through all files and retrieve updates to the folder, following the same rules as documented for {@link DbxUserFilesRequests#listFolder(String)}. cursor: The cursor returned by your last call to {@link DbxUserFilesRequests#listFolder(String)} or {@link DbxUserFilesRequests#listFolderContinue(String)}. Must have length of at least 1 and not be {@code null}.

method.name: copy
method.comment: Copy a file or folder to a different location in the user's Dropbox. If the source path is a folder all its contents will be copied. fromPath: toPath: DEV:not tested!

method.name: listFolder
method.comment:
Lists the content from path "path" - If "includeDeleted" is set to true then deleted files/folders are listed too. See Metadata for details on each entry.
- is "includeHasExplicitSharedMembers" is set to true then "i dont know what happens ;) See Dropbox site for more info ;-)
- if "includeMediaInfo" is set to true then the result will ontain MediaInfo too (pictures and video)
- If "recursive" is set to true then the Folder will be listed recursively. Note that this could result in a long list of Metadatas.
- If "debuglog" is set to true then the lib will do some LOG-Output so see where it hangs
DEV:Tested!

method.name: GetMetadata
method.comment: Returns the metadata for a file or folder. Note: Metadata for the root folder is unsupported. path: DEV:not tested!

property.name: EmailVerified
property.comment: Whether the user has verified their e-mail address.

property.name: TeamMemberId
property.comment: The user's unique team member id. This field will only be present if the user is part of a team and {@link BasicAccount#getIsTeammate} is {@code true}.

property.name: AccountId
property.comment: The user's unique Dropbox ID.

property.name: Email
property.comment: The user's e-mail address. Do not rely on this without checking the {@link Account#getEmailVerified} field. Even then, it's possible that the user has since lost access to their e-mail.

property.name: IsTeammate
property.comment: Whether this user is a teammate of the current user. If this account is the current user's account, then this will be {@code true}.

property.name: Disabled
property.comment: Whether the user has been disabled.

property.name: ProfilePhotoUrl
property.comment: URL for the photo representing the user, if one is set.

property.name: Name
property.comment: Details of a user's name.

property.name: Locale
property.comment: The language that the user specified. Locale tags will be IETF language tags.

property.comment: The user's unique Dropbox ID.

property.comment: The user's e-mail address. Do not rely on this without checking the {@link Account#getEmailVerified} field. Even then, it's possible that the user has since lost access to their e-mail.

property.name: IsPaired
property.comment: Whether the user has a personal and work account. If the current account is personal, then {@link FullAccount#getTeam} will always be {@code null}, but {@link FullAccount#getIsPaired} will indicate if a work account is linked.

property.name: AccountType

property.name: Name

property.name: EmailVerified

property.name: TeamMemberId
property.comment: This account's unique team member id. This field will only be present if {@link FullAccount#getTeam} is present.

property.name: Country
property.comment: The user's two-letter country code, if available. Country codes are based on ISO 3166-1.

property.name: Team
property.comment: If this account is a member of a team, information about that team.

property.name: ReferralLink
property.comment: The user's referral link.

property.name: Disabled

property.name: ProfilePhotoUrl

property.name: FamiliarName
property.comment: Locale-dependent name. In the US, a person's familiar name is their {@link Name#getGivenName}, but elsewhere, it could be any combination of a person's {@link Name#getGivenName} and {@link Name#getSurname}.

property.name: DisplayName
property.comment: A name that can be used directly to represent the name of a user's Dropbox account.

property.name: GivenName
property.comment: Also known as a first name.

property.name: Surname
property.comment: Also known as a last name or family name.

property.name: AbbreviatedName
property.comment: An abbreviated form of the person's name. Their initials in most locales.
